} Listing 16-5: Using the move keyword to force a closure to take ownership of the values it uses What would happen to the code in Listing 16-4 where the main thread called drop if we use a move closure? Would move fix that case? Unfortunately, no; we would get a different error because what Listing 16-4 is trying to do isn’t allowed for a different reason. If we added move to the closure, we would move v into the closure’s environment, and we could no longer call drop on it in the main thread. We would get this compiler error instead: $ cargo run Compiling threads v0.1.0 (file:///projects/threads)
