We’ll look at how a slow-processing request can affect other requests made to our current server implementation. Listing 20-10 implements handling a request to /sleep with a simulated slow response that will cause the server to sleep for 5 seconds before responding. Filename: src/main.rs # use std::fs;
# use std::io::prelude::*;
# use std::net::TcpListener;
